00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
I'm telling you, ladies and gentlemen, there's power in the body of Christ if we join together and pray.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
And that's why I do these even more because I think we're seeing change.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
We feel it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
So, knowing that, I'm expecting a change in this political situation this week that we are not going to see craziness on Saturday.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
We don't want buildings burning down.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.150
I don't want to see all that: Walmart, Target, and wherever else they want to pillage—Costco, Kroger, Sam's—going in there and starting to steal everything before this Christmas season.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
It would cause mass chaos in our nation with martial law.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
I don't want the police telling me when I have to go home.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
What if I want to go out and get something to eat?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
You have to go home by 7 o'clock?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
You can't; it's dark outside.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
No way, man.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.600
We're free for a reason, and we're not going to have knuckleheads come in here and destroy our cities so that President Trump would have to have martial law because they don't have their food stamps.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
We need these politicians to do what they're called to do.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
Do your job so we don't have all this craziness in our nation.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
41 million people are on food stamps right now.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
That is sad.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
That's a lot of people—more than 10% of our nation on food stamps.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
Now, I don't know if all those people need to have them, but it's not my call.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
It's not my job.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
So if they believe they need them and they need help, then by all means.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I had food stamps for a long time.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
We couldn't have lived if it wasn't for those food stamps.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
When we were living on minimum wage with our kids, we depended on it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
We were excited when we got that every month.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
I remember we were scared when you'd think, 'Well, you got to stretch it,' and we would stretch it because we were living paycheck to paycheck.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
We didn't have anything, and I thank God for that government when they helped us.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
It was rough, but it was a blessing.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
Back then, we thanked God for it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
I don't ever condemn anybody because I was there for years, and it was like God helped me being a janitor.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
We lived by paychecks and we didn't even have it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
We were so thankful for those food stamps.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
I don't ever sit here and beat on anybody's head because I lived it for more than 10 years, and God provided, and we are thankful.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
I know what it's like to not have that on the first and think, 'Oh my gosh.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
' So I'm never going to poke anybody.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
I know exactly.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
There's always going to be people in every situation that abuse stuff, but there are people that rightfully need that help.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Yeah, because I was there.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Thank God.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
It bought our meat.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
It bought our bread.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
It bought our peanut butter.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
It bought everything we needed for that month.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
The church didn't pay us much, but we made it and God provided.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
We made it through.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
So we don't want the people to go without on the first.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
I can't imagine what we would have done back then.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
If they say, 'Well, are you going to have it?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
' we would have to go out and get another job and do more and more work even making what we had.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Thank God for it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
It's pride.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
You know, a lot of times as a man, you don't want to have to do that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
You think, 'Oh God, you've been a lousy husband or a lousy father.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
' It was not that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
I worked my tail end off; I just didn't have an education at the time.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
God has been faithful to Brandon.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
So we love you all and we want to thank you for joining us tonight.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Paisley wants to say hi.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
'Hi, everybody.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Hi, everybody.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
' She's a good kid.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
One day I'll let you on here, but not now.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Do they have any questions?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
That's it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Nope.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Well, we love you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
Remember, thank you for praying for us and praying with us.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Yes.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
We'll see you again tomorrow.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
We'll keep praying.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
I felt I should keep praying.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.400
It's been interesting because it's been about the October 31st praying, every day really trying to hit this hard to get this government back open and get this budget passed so we don't have craziness because I've already told you the result of it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
But I already know God has a plan, and we're going to stop this in the name of Jesus.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
And we're not going to allow our nation to get burned up and get craziness.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
We're going to believe God for revival.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
But remember, put a smile on your face, song in your heart.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
Jesus loves you so much and we love you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
God bless you and we'll see you again soon.
